    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/fda-cdrh-biomechanics-reviewer",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility level. One factor (Test conditions) achieved Gradation 2 against required Gradation 3 due to single ASTM F1717 load configuration; this gap is accepted given that all three QoIs passed quantitative acceptance criteria (percent difference <10%, E/uval <1.96) and the test condition is the regulatory standard. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
